rComments: Had him as a TA for ENG 110. His tutorial quickly became my favourite class. He would give us specific instructions for our paper, and was accessible to talk to about our graded essays. Will forever be grateful for his guidance through my first year.
Low-stress course yet learned a lot.

Professor Murray quickly became one of my favorites. He's hilarious during lectures - manages to counter dull information with these entertaining jokes or videos. What he teaches goes beyond what you'd expect from the course; he's really inspirational. He can be monotonous and a strict grader, but I still loved his lectures. Definitely amazing.

As a TA for this class, he is responsible for marking the assignment and the essay. Hard marker. His feedbacks made me like, "... really?" - quite debatable comments. Heard from a few that it takes him long to reply emails. The prof says one thing, but when he marks, it is a totally different thing.

Lectures are boring, very monotone, found his analysis/explanations not detailed, full enough. But if you have a keen interest in the books/topics then you could to do well. There was almost weekly quizzes. The 2 essay assignments were graded very tough (graded by a different prof). The course topic was ok/interesting but would not take again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Beware of pop quizzes']
